         public static final String CONST_DOT_FAQ_CONTENT1 ="A parachain is a feature of the Polkadot multi-chain network. It is considered a simpler form of blockchain. A parachain works by attaching to the security provided by a Relay Chain rather than providing its own. By doing this, all parachains benefit from the Relay Chain’s base features.";
         public static final String CONST_DOT_FAQ_CONTENT2 ="The heart of Polkadot, the Relay Chain, is responsible for coordinating the system as a whole. This includes the network’s shared security, consensus and cross-chain interoperability. It is composed of a relatively small number of transaction types that include ways to interact with the governance mechanism, parachain auctions, and participating in NPoS.";
         public static final String CONST_DOT_FAQ_CONTENT3 ="Bridges are what allow the Polkadot network to interact with other blockchains. With bridges, tokens can be swapped without the need for a central exchange.";
